Some morning charts for you.  In red are the six prior times since 1953 that the S&P fell 10%+ from an all-time high in four weeks or less (like it just did).  Notice anything?

By 2040, 90% of all car sales in China will have self-driving capabilities, compared with nearly 80% in Europe and about 65% in America, reckons Goldman Sachs.

The country’s carmakers are pushing for their “ChatGPT moment”
The volatility is more extreme but the way this market has tracked year three (so far) of prior long-term bull markets is impressive.
These charts got hit with the ugly stick.
